00:27.280 --> 00:34.240
view because anyone who does research in applied linguistics at whatever level, whether that is

00:34.240 --> 00:44.640
your BA research project or your MA dissertation or your PhD or any project beyond the PhD,

00:45.360 --> 00:55.520
everybody is facing similar issues and of course the expectations change slightly as you progress

00:55.600 --> 01:07.520
through your career. I would start by talk about some, I would say almost philosophical issues

01:07.520 --> 01:18.640
about research and one of the things that always struck me was that students tend to have,

01:19.520 --> 01:30.560
tend to believe in predeterminism. They see these libraries full of books and these journals full

01:30.560 --> 01:39.440
of papers and they can see the publication lists of certain researchers and it's easy to think

01:39.440 --> 01:52.800
that this was destined to happen and so that it was driven by God, faith or some unknown force

01:53.920 --> 02:04.880
so they tend to underestimate the fact that in fact nothing is predetermined. If you're a researcher

02:04.880 --> 02:11.840
you could go in a thousand different directions, you could ask a thousand different questions and

02:11.840 --> 02:20.080
you have a choice between a huge amount of methods and so nothing of what actually is produced

02:20.720 --> 02:28.960
is predetermined. It's the result of free choice, free spirits trying to do something

02:28.960 --> 02:36.880
that they are interested in and so I would say that it's crucial to hence realize that

02:37.760 --> 02:45.360
Lambert, Garner, Dornier to mention three of the biggest names in motivation research and second

02:45.360 --> 02:52.800
language acquisition that they weren't destined to introduce motivation and I had a chat with

02:52.800 --> 03:01.040
Garner and Dornier and they were kind of surprised to a certain degree by the fact that their papers

03:01.040 --> 03:08.320
seemed to have so much impact. They hadn't necessarily anticipated it. They were also

03:08.320 --> 03:14.880
interested in other things but it was motivation that made their name and so I quite like the little

03:15.440 --> 03:24.240
picture there about the PhD. If you're standing at the door deciding what to do for your PhD

03:24.240 --> 03:30.800
it may look like a maze and I totally agree and I think that in fact the first year of doing the

03:30.800 --> 03:39.360
